Step-by-Step Execution in Exam
✅ STEP 1 — Create New Project

Open Android Studio → New Project
Select Empty Activity
Name: MediaPlayerDemo
Package: com.example.mediaplayerdemo
Language: Java
Min SDK: API 21
Click Finish → Wait for Gradle


✅ STEP 2 — Create raw Folder and Add MP3 ⭐ MOST CRITICAL STEP

In left panel: Right-click res folder
New → Android Resource Directory
Resource type: select raw from dropdown
Click OK
Now Right-click the new raw folder → Show in Explorer
Copy-paste any .mp3 file into that folder
Rename it to: song.mp3 (must be lowercase!)
Come back to Android Studio — it auto-detects


✅ STEP 3 — Edit activity_main.xml

Go to: res → layout → activity_main.xml
Click Code tab → Replace everything with XML below


✅ STEP 4 — Edit MainActivity.java

Open MainActivity.java → Replace everything with Java code below


✅ STEP 5 — Run the App

Click Run ▶️ → Select emulator → OK
App opens → Click Play → Music starts!
